text: Beann Eadair GAA is a Gaelic Athletic Association club in based in Howth, Fingal. The club has an adult men's and ladies football team and boys' and girls' underage football hurling and camogie teams at various levels. ==History== ==Achievements== * Dublin Junior Football Championship: (1) 1974 ==External links== * Category:Gaelic Athletic Association clubs in Fingal Category:Gaelic football clubs in Fingal
